description.p:
a form which has a section shaped according to said predetermined profile and operated perpendicularly with respect to its longitudinal axis;


a stop that faces said form, so that said form, while lowering, clamps said sheet piece to be formed and resting on said support means, to said stop;


two plates oscillating on a vertical plane transversal to said form;


two spindles fitted to said plates and arranged parallel to said form and at either sides of said stop;


two bending members rotating about said spindles, said bending members being operated in time relation with a synchronous movement of said form and said stop, to fold the two ends of said sheet round said form.

The characteristics of the invention are pointed out in the following description, with particular reference to the enclosed drawings, in which:


